ÿ
û
        Yes, the prices were a little steep in the first one. The first
    thing I said to Paul Gumsley when Carl released the first issue of my
    magazine, was that no-one was going to pay those kind of prices - and
    I was right. Because of the lack of correspondence that he gave me, I
    dropped Carl from the team, and began ranning EA as I did the old
    Mushroom PD magazine. The second issue was a rush-job, as it was four
    days before the release date when I began programming that engine, as
    Carl left me with nothing to use. It also explains the poor quality of
    graphics.
    
        As for the price of adverts and messages, well I have abolished
    the scheme, as I never had a "Pay to Place" system before. All I ask
    of advertisers, or message leavers, is that they send me an AMOS
    article. wether it be a simple review of a latest AMOS extension, or
    game, or maybe even a tutorial for a particular subject or command. If
    you are sending lot's of pictures/messages in, then it would be nice
    to receive a few articles, or a first class stamp.
    
    
    
ÿ
